  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Reverse Integer\n\nReverse the decimal digits of a signed 32-bit integer. Return `0` if the reversed value overflows the signed 32-bit range.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: x = 123\nOutput: 321\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: x = -120\nOutput: -21\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: x = 1534236469\nOutput: 0\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Use direct arithmetic, matrix indexing, or bit operations to preserve the required invariants while keeping extra state small.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def reverse(self, x):\n        sign = -1 if x < 0 else 1\n        value = int(str(abs(x))[::-1]) * sign\n        return value if -2 ** 31 <= value <= 2 ** 31 - 1 else 0\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Watch fixed-width integer boundaries where the prompt requires them.",
    "For matrix mutation, mark or capture affected rows and columns before overwriting."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def reverse(self, x):\n        pass\n"
  },
